        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"mrandr01d\" data-post=\"1\" data-topic=\"68283\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/m/f08c70/48.png\" class=\"avatar\"> mrandr01d:</div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>How does signal behave if there are pending scheduled messages and the device reboots?</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Rebooting doesnâ€™t clear scheduled messages. My phone reboots every couple days and they are retained.</p>\n<p>I also scheduled a message several years ago to send around February this year, and it sent successfully. So scheduled messages stay valid within the local backup file on Android.</p>",
